2 <!--33-->Saruman&#39;s Power    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok I do not use Son of Hamfast because I want Sam to FIGHT! For that end, Halfling Deftness and There and Back Again do well. I&#39;m using Intuitions rather than Stealths because I want to kill my opponents. Hopefully by doing so I can double move somewhere between 3 and 6. Boromir just does what he does best; cook medium well orc steaks. There&#39;s Aragorn and a lone Pippin in case somebody dies, something you should always be prepared for.<br />
<br />
On the Shadow side, you&#39;re probably thinking: no Tower of Orthanc? Well, I don&#39;t like it as it is a Sleep/Sentinels target and is lost to my own Saruman&#39;s Powers, a must have card. Orc Commander is da bomb! Between him, Axes, and Servants to Saruman, I can actually win skirmishes without relying on chancey Saruman tactics. If I don&#39;t, Trapped and Alone will bail me out against everybody but Gimli.<br />
<br />
This deck may be advanced due to the number of rares, but it should still be someting you play for the fun of it. I mean, when you get an opening and wipe somebody with the &quot;weak&quot; Isengard Orcs, and they&#39;re thinking, &quot;how the heck did I lose to THAT?&quot;, how priceless is that? </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
